sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Browser as Browser User
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OIDC as OIDC / OpenShift<br/>OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant APIClient as API Client
    participant Upstream as Upstream App

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: OAuth2/OIDC Browser Authentication (auth mode)
        Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/start<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        AuthProxy->>AuthProxy: Generate PKCE code_verifier<br/>+ CSRF cookie (signed)
        AuthProxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OIDC authorize
        Browser->>OIDC: GET /authorize<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>client_id + PKCE challenge
        OIDC->>Browser: Login page → User authenticates
        OIDC->>Browser: 302 Redirect with auth code
        Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback?code=XXX<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        AuthProxy->>OIDC: POST /token<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>client_credentials + auth_code + PKCE verifier
        OIDC-->>AuthProxy: ID Token + Access Token + Refresh Token
        AuthProxy->>Redis: Store session (ticket-based)<br/>TCP 6379 (optional)
        AuthProxy-->>Browser: Set-Cookie (AES-encrypted session)<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        Browser->>AuthProxy: GET / with session cookie<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        AuthProxy->>AuthProxy: Validate session, refresh if needed
        AuthProxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>+ GAP-Auth headers
        Upstream-->>AuthProxy: Response
        AuthProxy-->>Browser: Proxied response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over APIClient,Upstream: Flow 2: Kubernetes RBAC Authorization (rbac mode)
        APIClient->>RBACProxy: Request with Bearer token<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
        RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>SA token auth
        K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: TokenReview result (user identity)
        RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>SA token auth
        K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: SubjectAccessReview result (allow/deny)
        alt Authorized
            RBACProxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS/h2c<br/>+ auth headers (optional)
            Upstream-->>RBACProxy: Response
            RBACProxy-->>APIClient: Proxied response
        else Denied
            RBACProxy-->>APIClient: 403 Forbidden
        end
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 3: K8s ServiceAccount Token (auth mode)
        APIClient->>AuthProxy: Request with K8s SA Bearer token<br/>HTTPS/4443 TLS 1.2+
        AuthProxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>audiences: configured list
        K8sAPI-->>AuthProxy: TokenReview result (user identity)
        AuthProxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>+ proxied user identity
        Upstream-->>AuthProxy: Response
        AuthProxy-->>APIClient: Proxied response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 240)
        Note over Browser,OIDC: Flow 4: OpenShift OAuth Logout with Token Deletion
        Browser->>AuthProxy: POST /oauth2/sign_out<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Session cookie
        AuthProxy->>K8sAPI: DELETE /apis/oauth.openshift.io/v1/oauthaccesstokens/{name}<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>User's access token (Bearer)
        K8sAPI-->>AuthProxy: 200 OK (token deleted)
        AuthProxy->>Redis: Delete session<br/>TCP 6379 (optional)
        AuthProxy-->>Browser: Clear cookie + Redirect to IdP logout
    end
